{
  "texts": [
    "This preference stability is crucial for product developers, providing a reliable foundation for creating popular food products.",
    "The differences in sensory processing lead to variations in consumer behavior related to taste and smell.",
    "Olfactory preferences are often shaped by personal experiences, cultural backgrounds, and even genetics, which can create considerable diversity in how scents are perceived.",
    "For example, while some may find particular food aromas appealing, others might have aversions based on past associations or sensitivities.",
    "In olfactory branding, marketers frequently capitalize on these emotional connections tied to scents to enhance customer loyalty and product recall."
  ]
}